{"title": "The Producer Thinks of Everything", "content": "Please don't list this on a work's page as a trope. Examples can go on the work's YMMV tab.\n\n\"I think there are two types of writers, the architects and the gardeners. The architects plan everything ahead of time, like an architect building a house. They know how many rooms are going to be in the house, what kind of roof they're going to have, where the wires are going to run, what kind of plumbing there's going to be. They have the whole thing designed and blueprinted out before they even nail the first board up.\"\n\nThis trope concerns where the Production Team has clearly Shown Their Work in regards to the entire show, but more so than just that.\n\nIf your TV show has plenty of Chekhov's Gun, Chekhov's Gunman, Chekhov's Armory, A Batman Gambit or two, Arc Words, Myth Arcs, and the Early-Bird Cameo, chances are your show is in the hands of a production team that goes above and beyond the call of duty to create a truly memorable and deeply detailed experience. Not to be confused with an actual plan or the Myth Arc itself. Other signs of the producers foreseeing everything would include introducing plot points far before they become important, possible sneak peeks of characters in the Pilot Episode, and a generally close attention to detail that you wouldn't find on just any show. This is about not only careful planning, but also anticipating and routing around troubles such as Real Life Writes the Plot and Executive Meddling.\n\nProducers and the Creative Talent behind the show are the key here. This trope does NOT concern the in-universe or in-story examples of characters planning things out to a ridiculous degree.\n\nOften overlaps with Doing It for the Art. Compare Developers' Foresight for when a creator of interactive media puts in creative edge cases for obscure scenarios, and contrast Truth in Television Indy Ploys and Writing by the Seat of Your Pants for when they have almost no idea where things may lead to, leading to The Chris Carter Effect.\n\nHas nothing to do with a Crazy-Prepared Parker Kovak.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheProducerThinksOfEverything", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/GeorgeRRMartin", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/ProducingParker", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FullmetalAlchemist", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/NaokiUrasawa", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/RahXephon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/SmilePrettyCure", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/OnePiece", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/PandoraHearts", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/AstroBoy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/YuGiOhArcV", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Transformers", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/MegaMan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/IanFlynn", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MegaManX", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SuperAdventureRockman", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MegaMan3", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/UniversalWarOne", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Unfriended", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/YouTube", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/HowToTrainYourDragon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/StarWars", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/RevengeOfTheSith", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/AttackOfTheClones", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/CatchTwentyTwo", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/HarryPotter", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/WarriorCats", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheDresdenFiles", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/JimButcher", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/StormFront", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Changes", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheCosmere", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/BrandonSanderson", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/JMichaelStraczynski", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BabylonFive", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Fringe", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/AmericanIdol", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Carnivale", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/ArrestedDevelopment", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Degrassi", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/QI", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/BillBailey", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.p